HEADWORD: Delundung
<hw>De*lun"dung</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An East Indian carnivorous mammal
(<spn>Prionodon gracilis</spn>), resembling the civets, but without
scent pouches. It is handsomely spotted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

